Implementation details for P3.2 - Runtime Cost Monitoring:

## Architecture Decisions
- Background goroutine with configurable check interval (default: 1 hour)
- Callbacks for alerts and teardown allow flexible integration
- Auto-teardown disabled by default for safety
- Stats tracking for observability (alerts sent, teardowns done)

## Key Components Added
1. CostMonitor - main monitoring struct with Start/Stop lifecycle
2. MonitorConfig - configuration options (interval, callbacks, auto-teardown)
3. MonitorStats - runtime statistics
4. AlertLevel enum - none/warning/critical/exceeded
5. SpendingAlert - rich alert context with message formatting

## API Methods
- NewCostMonitor(cfg, limits, config) - constructor
- Start(ctx) / Stop() - lifecycle management
- CheckNow(ctx) - on-demand check
- IsRunning() / LastRunTime() / LastError() / Stats() - introspection

## Alert Logic
- Warning: 90% of alert threshold reached
- Critical: alert threshold reached (default 80%)
- Exceeded: over budget limit
- Auto-teardown only triggers on Exceeded for specific deployments (not TOTAL)

## Integration Points
- Uses CostTracker.GenerateMonitoringReport() for data
- TeardownCallback integrates with aws_teardown tool
- AlertCallback for custom notification systems (email, Slack, etc.)

## Testing Strategy
